The Simple Genius of Emacs Registers It&rsquo;s been in emacs since the beginning, and is not had in many other editors, yet many people don&rsquo;t know about it. Registers. The documentation talks about many types, most of which I haven&rsquo;t tried yet. The three I use the most, however, are:
  Text in register. Suppose I want a chunk of text but am doing something that will pollute my kill ring, so I can&rsquo;t just yank (paste) every time.